@NODE purpose "Purpose"

    Purpose:

    The Purpose of this program is that you can check if you have your
    cdrom/scanner or other scsi device turned on. This program give a
    standard RETURN_OK or RETURN_FAIL/RETURN_WARN return value.
    Based on the return value you can perform some conditional actions
    in your startup-sequence, like mounting a device when the device is 
    available, etc. 
    I mount my devices from DEVS:DosDrivers, but when I forgot to turn 
    my CDROM on I always got a lot of problems by the device handler. So
    when I didn't want my CDROM to be mounted, I had to move the MountFile
    CD0 to SYS:Storage/DosDrivers. 


@ENDNODE
@NODE usage "Usage"

    Usage:

    ExistsSCSIDEV DEVICE/K,UNIT/K/N,TYPE/K,VERBOSE/S,HELP/S

    DEVICE:    device name, <scsi.device> is default
    UNIT       unit number, <2> is default
    TYPE       device type, <CDROM> is default
    VERBOSE    extra info
    HELP       help info

      TYPE:           Code:  Description:

      DIRECT          00h    Direct-access device (e.g. magnetic disk) 
      SEQUENTIAL      01h    Sequential-access device (e.g. magnetic tape)
      PRINTER         02h    Printer device
      CPU             03h    Processor device
      WRITEONCE       04h    Write-once device (e.g. some optical disks)
      CDROM           05h    CD-ROM device
      SCANNER         06h    Scanner device
      OPTICALMEM      07h    Optical memory device (e.g. some optical disks)
      MEDIUMCHGR      08h    Medium changer device (e.g. jukeboxes)
      COMM            09h    Communications device
      ASC1IT8         0Ah    Defined by ASC IT8 (Graphic arts pre-press devices)
      ASC2IT8         0Bh    Defined by ASC IT8 (Graphic arts pre-press devices)
      RESERVED1       0Ch    Reserved
      ...             ...    Reserved
      RESERVED19      1Eh    Reserved
      UNKNOWN         1Fh    Unknown or no device type

    
      VERBOSE:

      gives out extra information. If you don't know what type your
      device is, you will get information about the type which was found.
      example of verbose output:

      SCSI-2 Compiliant Device           <-- SCSI-1 or SCSI-2 device type
      Wanted Device: CD-ROM device       <-- Wanted device type description
      Parsed Type Argument: CDROM        <-- Wanted device type argument

      Actual Device Found: CD-ROM device <-- Found device type description
      Required Type Argument: CDROM      <-- Found device type argument
      SANYO   CRD-250S        Rev:1.19   <-- Inquiry Data from found device

    Example: ExistsSCSIDEV DEVICE scsi.device UNIT 2 TYPE CDROM VERBOSE


@ENDNODE
