@NODE install "Installation"

    Installation:

    Copy the ExistsSCSIDEV program to the C: directory, and copy the Guide
    file to the HELP: directory. The Guide file is not needed by the
    program, but exists for your convenience only.

    Change you startup-sequence to something like this, change it according
    your requirements.

      ExistsSCSIDEV DEVICE scsi.device UNIT 2 TYPE CDROM
      IF NOT WARN
        ; copy the mount icon for your device from the dosdrivers storage
        Copy SYS1:Storage/DosDrivers/CD0 devs:DosDrivers QUIET
        Copy SYS1:Storage/DosDrivers/CD0.info devs:DosDrivers QUIET
      EndIf

      IF EXISTS SYS:Devs/DOSDrivers
        Mount >NIL: SYS:Devs/DosDrivers/~(#?.info)
      EndIF

      IF EXISTS Devs:DosDrivers/CD0
        ; delete the mount icon, so that this will work the next time 
        Delete Devs:DosDrivers/CD0 Devs:DosDrivers/CD0.info QUIET
      EndIf

    Another possibility is that you use ExistsSCSIDEV in the following way.

      ExistsSCSIDEV DEVICE scsi.device UNIT 2 TYPE CDROM
      IF NOT WARN
        ; mount your device
        mount CD0:
      EndIf
   
@ENDNODE
